title.narrative: LAND ADMINISTRATION AND MANAGEMENT II PROJECT

description.narrative: The project development objectives are to increase land tenure security and improve land administration services through the implementation of institutional and legal reform, the realization of an accelerated land titling program, and the establishment of a fair and uniform property valuation system.

condition.narrative: Appoint and maintain, during the execution of the Project, the National Steering Committee
Carry out an initial baseline study, in order to provide quantitative benchmarks for assessing socio-economic and environmentalimp act indicators and carry out a follow-up survey nlt 06/30/10
Cause each Selected Province and Selected City to appoint and maintain, during the execution of the Project, a local steeringcommit tee within said Selected Province and Selected City
Develop and adopt minimum service standards for the operation of OSS, covering, inter alia, registration and land transactions,appr oval of survey plans and first time land title issuance
Employ the services of an independent monitor, as shall be required for the monitoring of the compliance with minimum servicesstand ards by OSS
Establish and maintain during the execution of the Project, Project Implementation Units (PIU) in Selected Provinces and SelectedCi ties
Establish and maintain during the execution of the Project, Regional Project Implementation Units (RPIU) in Selected Regions
Establish and maintain within DENR, during the execution of the Project, a Unified Project Management Office (UPMO) and a projectco ordination unit
Establish and maintain within DOF, during the execution of the Project, a project management office
Financial statements to be audited by indepeendent auditors acceptable to the Bank
Furnish quarterly FMRs of DENR and DOF to the Bank, not later than 45 days after each calendar qtr
Furnish to the Bank, for its review and comments, a draft annual work plan and budget
Maintain a FMS and preparte financial statements in accordance with consistently applied accounting standards.
Prepare and adopt a monitoring and evaluation system for the carrying out of its obligations
Review with Bank MTR Report
Review with Bank, six monthly M&E report
Review with the Bank, the ICR report, and, thereafter, take all measures required to ensure sustainability of the Projectachieveme nts
Submit MTR report
Submit an external terminal evaluation report integrating the results of the M&E activities performed pursuant to sub-paragraph(a)o f this paragraph 6
Submit six monthly M&E report
Through DENR, select the provinces, cities and municipalities of the Borrower that will participate in Part C of the Project asSele cted Provinces, Cities, and Municipalities
Through DOF, select the provinces, cities and municipalities of the Borrower that will participate in Part D.2 of the Project

title.narrative: Increase in collectible revenue from property and other land-related taxes

comment.narrative: # Revenues from land transactions at the LGU level (RPT) is deemed low largely due to incomplete cadastral survey and mapping, thenon-declaration of property via tax declaration, high percentage of absentee land owners and lackluster support for tax mapping andinformation drive
Increase has no specific % target to be achieved.
Overall increases in all project locations ranging from 120-360% over the life of the project.

title.narrative: Increased investment in land property development

comment.narrative: About 30% of the total respondents have investment in land property development# Investment may vary but mostly it is amountingtoless than P50,000
Increase has no specific % target to be achieved.

Dropped under AF and under project restructuring agreed MTR.It may not attributable to this project. There are too many variablefactors to attributeincreased investment in land property development to LAMP2.

title.narrative: Decrease in informal and formal transaction costs in land registration process

comment.narrative: An average cost of 7,118.5 was spent per application
Increase has no specific % target to be achieved.
This indicator was dropped due to the extreme difficulty of realistically being able to measure such an indicator - agreed at MTR.

EMPLOYMENT (On-farm employment; off-farm employment; non-farm employment); FARM BUSINESS; NON-FARM BUSINESS (wholesale/retailbusiness; manufacturing; community, social, recreational & personal services; transportation & communication; forestry, mining &quarrying); OTHERS (remittances from abroad; local remittances; pension, retirement, benefits; rental income; interest earnings,dividends, capital gains; inheritance; winnings from games of chance); # OTHERS
Increase has no specific % target to be achieved.

Dropped under AF and also under project restructuring agreed at MTR.# It is not attributable to this project. There are too manyvariable factors to attributeincreased investment inland property development to LAMP2.

title.narrative: Increase in subsequent transactions registered in OSS

comment.narrative: Fourteen percent or 86 out of the 612 titles have registered subsequent transactions after the issuance of the OCT
Increase has no specific % target to be achieved.
The OSS operations were replaced by the government's LARES project and the work under LAMS. Thus no longer part of LAMP2.

It is recognized that titled lands command higher land values, are easier to sell and can be offered as collateral in securingloans from formal sources .Comparative values between titled and untitled lands also show that among owners, titled lands arevalued three times more than untitled lands. P29,744 to P4,950,000 .Prices of titled parcel is perceived by majority to be higherthan the untitled parcel. Price difference between titled and untitled ranges from 6% to 41%. Land values range fromPhp135,000-Php210,000 perha .
Increase has no specific % target to be achieved.
This indicator cannot be reliably measured. Dropped under AF and under project restructuring agreed MTR.
